    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/useful_links/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/useful_links/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here I&amp;rsquo;ve collated useful links that may come in handy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Finding papers:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;NASA Astronomical Data System&lt;/a&gt; - a search engine for finding papers&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/list/astro-ph.GA/recent&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;arxiv&lt;/a&gt; - open access repository for the latest astronomy papers, beware - some of these mightn&amp;rsquo;t have been refereed yet!&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/publications-of-the-astronomical-society-of-australia/dawes-review&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Dawes reviews&lt;/a&gt; - a series of papers reviewing topical areas of astronomy comissioned by the Publications of the Astronomical Society of Australia.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Galaxies:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://astronomy.nmsu.edu/drewski/tableofemissionlines.html&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Emission line list&lt;/a&gt; - what&amp;rsquo;s that line? it&amp;rsquo;s one of these.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.astro.ucla.edu/~wright/CosmoCalc.html&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Cosmology calculator&lt;/a&gt; - get information for objects based on redshift and chosen cosmology&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ned.ipac.caltech.edu/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Nasa Extragalactic Database&lt;/a&gt; - everything you need to know about an object.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://catserver.ing.iac.es/staralt/index.php&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Staralt&lt;/a&gt; - object visibility plotter&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Python:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Galaxies @ UniSQ</title>
      <link>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/group/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/group/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;person-card&#34; style=&#34;display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:center;margin:1rem 0;&#34;&gt;&lt;img&#xA;      src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/group/space_award_hu_1fa4439e430d2910.webp&#34;&#xA;      alt=&#34;Dr Rebecca McElroy&#34;&#xA;      width=&#34;600&#34; height=&#34;539&#34;&#xA;      loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;      style=&#34;border-radius:9999px;width:clamp(120px,18vw,200px);height:clamp(120px,18vw,200px);object-fit:cover;&#34;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h3 style=&#34;margin:0 0 .25rem 0;&#34;&gt;Dr Rebecca McElroy&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;opacity:.7;margin-bottom:.25rem;&#34;&gt;Group Lead&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&#34;margin:.25rem 0;&#34;&gt;Leads the Close AGN Reference Survey (CARS) investigating the physics of nearby active galaxies. Co-chair of the LSST AGN Science Collaboration’s Watchlist and Follow-up Working Groups, and member of the HECTOR team - an Australian next-generation integral-field spectrograph for galaxy evolution studies.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div style=&#34;display:flex;gap:.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:rebecca.mcelroy@unisq.edu.au&#34;&gt;Email&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;person-card&#34; style=&#34;display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:center;margin:1rem 0;&#34;&gt;&lt;img&#xA;      src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/group/thomas_hu_ad040b18b53bef07.webp&#34;&#xA;      alt=&#34;Thomas Dunn&#34;&#xA;      width=&#34;600&#34; height=&#34;600&#34;&#xA;      loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;      style=&#34;border-radius:9999px;width:clamp(120px,18vw,200px);height:clamp(120px,18vw,200px);object-fit:cover;&#34;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h3 style=&#34;margin:0 0 .25rem 0;&#34;&gt;Thomas Dunn&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;opacity:.7;margin-bottom:.25rem;&#34;&gt;PhD Student&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&#34;margin:.25rem 0;&#34;&gt;Combining archival photographic plates with contemporary multi-wavelength observations to build a century-long light curve of the changing-look active galaxies Mrk 1018. His work bridges historical datasets with modern time-domain astronomy to trace accretion-rate evolution over decades.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Outreach</title>
      <link>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/outreach/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/outreach/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;          alt=&#34;churchie&#34;&#xA;          width=&#34;2281&#34;&#xA;          height=&#34;863&#34;&#xA;          src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/churchie3_hu_f214bd5e96e0e973.JPG&#34;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/churchie3_hu_f214bd5e96e0e973.JPG 800w,/img/churchie3_hu_a588561ef0644016.JPG 1280w&#34;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/churchie3.JPG&#34;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;figcaption&gt;Delivering the keynote address at Churchie Physics Day.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;wrap-right-award&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;          alt=&#34;purple&#34;&#xA;          width=&#34;4032&#34;&#xA;          height=&#34;3024&#34;&#xA;          src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/purple_hu_2b773dafb98e03dc.jpg&#34;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/purple_hu_2b773dafb98e03dc.jpg 800w,/img/purple_hu_730ab9c5b6446cea.jpg 1280w&#34;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/purple.jpg&#34;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;figcaption&gt;Presenting at the Science and Engineering &amp;lsquo;Wear it Purple&amp;rsquo; event in 2025.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Need an astronomy expert? I do frequent outreach work in schools, pubs, on the radio, and occasionally even on TV.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am a passionate advocate for underrepresented groups in science. In my capacity as a queer disabled woman, I believe it is important to be visible and to share my experiences so that young people from similar backgrounds can see that a career in science is possible. In recognition of this I was awarded a Queensland Museum award for Breaking Barriers in STEM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Study @ UniSQ</title>
      <link>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/study_unisq/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/study_unisq/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img&#xA;    class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;    fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;UniSQ&#34;&#xA;    width=&#34;1200&#34;&#xA;    height=&#34;369&#34;&#xA;    src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/usq_hu_aebfc2ea9d2d5b45.png&#34;&#xA;    srcset=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/usq_hu_aebfc2ea9d2d5b45.png 800w, https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/usq.png 1280w&#34;&#xA;    sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xA;    data-zoom-src=&#34;https://rebeccamcelroy.github.io/img/usq.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Interested in studying Astronomy, Astrophysics, or Space Science? UniSQ is home to Queensland&amp;rsquo;s only professional observatory and the iLaunch programme, a collaboration of three universities and 20+ industry partners to boost Australia’s sovereign space capability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our world-class academics study astronomical objects from comets to quasars. In addition to hosting one of Australia&amp;rsquo;s largest exoplanet groups, we have scientists working on solar system objects, stars, galaxies, and black holes. I lead an extragalactic and active galaxies research group at UniSQ.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
